President Muhammadu Buhari is meeting with Governors elected under aegis of the All Progressive Congress ( APC) at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The meeting at the instance of the President is coming on the heels of recent crises rocking the party in various states controlled by the party. The party had been engulfed in crises with Governors squaring up against senators elected under the party’s platform. The meeting which is taking place at the First Lady’s wing of the Presidential Villa, is being attended by all the Governors elected under the aegis of the APC. Although the agenda of the meeting is not made public, inside sources said the President is displeased with the development that has engulfed the party, hence the meeting Details later.  Tony Ailemen, Abuja